On July 1, 2019, the President signed two laws into effect. The first is H.R. 3151, also known as the "Taxpayer First Act," which aims to improve the management and oversight of the Internal Revenue Service (IRS). The law includes measures to combat tax fraud, update the IRS's information technology systems, and make other changes to the Internal Revenue Code. The second law is H.R. 3401, the "Emergency Supplemental Appropriations for Humanitarian Assistance and Security at the Southern Border Act, 2019." This law provides additional funding for humanitarian assistance and security at the southern border for the fiscal year 2019.